Crisis at Melilla

July 12, 1909

From 1908 the troubled riffian cabilas of the Spanish Morocco were in revolt. They began the attacks on the spanish settlements by attacking the Spanish workers on the area, then, they could built up their irregular army by purchasing foreing weapons. Some tribal leaders claim for the holy war agaisnt Spain, and the riffian harkas (the moroccan irregular forces) put Melilla into real danger. 

Are you the proper commander to stop the moroccans at the gates of Melilla and save the Spanish international prestige and his men? Reinforcements from Spain are expected. At the first, save Melilla and the unarmed colonists, then, counterattack, and crush the rebel riffians.

20 Turns

